            <bug_when>2009-03-09 18:17:53 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>If a URL is encoded in the loader script like this:
&quot;C%3A/qooxdoo-0.8.2-sdk/framework/source/resource/&quot;
then the IE coudn&#39;t load the file from this URL.

But if the URL is encoded like this: 
&quot;C:/qooxdoo-0.8.2-sdk/framework/source/resource/&quot;
then the IE could load the file from the URL.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>10335</commentid>
            <who name="Thomas Herchenroeder">thron7</who>
            <bug_when>2009-06-09 15:47:29 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Whenever a Windows absolute path is to be used as a URI, &quot;file:&quot; is prepended,  
and the path is transformed using urllib.pathname2url(), which yields something 
 like &quot;///C|/a/...&quot;, with the path segments a, etc. url encoded.

With r19300.</thetext>
